      "data": {
        "markdown": "## 1990: Dr. Jerry France Goes to Eastern Europe\n\n### The Official Story\n\n**Radford University Project:**\n\"The final big project of the semester will be taking a group of students to Eastern Europe.\n\nWe will research the **expectations of men and women** as work life and day-to-day life change **after the wall came down**.\"\n\n### The Timing Problem\n\n**Fall of Berlin Wall → Immediate Chaos:**\n- Wall fell: 1989\n- Dr. France goes: **August 1990**\n- Yugoslav Wars begin: **Same year, August 1990**\n- \"Chaos and carnage\"\n\n**Candace's Question:**\n\"Imagine your kid's teacher says: 'We're going to go in 1990 to Eastern Europe after the wall came down.'\n\nDo you understand what happened after that? **Chaos. That's what happened.**\n\nAgain, why would you take students there to research **gender issues**?\n\nDo we think gender issues are ranking high in the minds of those Eastern Europeans?\"\n\n### Children in War\n\n**The Dark Reality:**\n\"Are you guys aware of how many children go missing during times of war?\n\nDuring all that chaos, how many kids are trafficked **during the fog of war**?\n\nI know this because one of my best friends in college was Romanian. She grew up with **real gypsies grabbing children off the street**.\n\nShe was almost trafficked as a child.\n\nWhere exactly are they taking these children? How could that go unnoticed?\"\n\n### Candace's Conclusion\n\n**Unequivocal Statement:**\n\n\"I don't think Dr. Jerry France, who is a **verifiable fraud**, was there in Eastern Europe researching gender issues.\n\nMay she rest in peace.\n\nBut that's my opinion and I'm sticking to it.\""
      }
    },
