      "data": {
        "markdown": "## The Pieces Come Together\n\n### April 2009: Lorie Establishes Charity\n\n**Everyday Heroes Like You**\n\nFiling claims:\n- Faith-based organization\n- Raising funds\n- **Developing programs for vulnerable children**\n\nPublished: July 2nd, 2009\n\n### Candace's Discomfort\n\n\"Lori seems a bit busy.\n\nShe's already working with the government. She's maybe in Afghanistan or at least creating tech for Afghanistan.\n\nAnd now, wow, this hero is jumping in: **'I'm going to help vulnerable children.'**\n\nWhy does that make me uncomfortable?\n\nDo I have a right to feel uncomfortable about that?\n\n**Military bases and doing stuff for the military and now 'I'm gonna help kids a little bit.'**\n\nMaybe I'm wrong. With everything I know about Lori, **I don't love it.**\"\n\n### October 2009: ROMANIA BASE ESTABLISHED\n\n**Romanian government agrees:**\nAllow America to set up military base along **Black Sea**\n\n### Erica's Claim: China Sex Trafficking Work\n\n**From \"Freethinkers Only\" Podcast:**\n\n\"Shortly after they established this charity, Everyday Heroes Like You, she's going to go to **China to help women who were sex trafficked**.\"\n\n**Timeline she gives:**\n1. Everyday Heroes comes first\n2. Goes to China (sex trafficking victims)\n3. Gets partnership with **Marines**\n4. Goes out and establishes **Romanian Angels project**\n\n**Candace:** \"Don't hold Erica to being consistent. You'll drive yourself crazy.\"\n\n### Also 2009: Erica Competes Miss Colorado\n\n**Problem:**\nBy her own standards, shouldn't be in Colorado anymore (\"first two years of school\")\n\nYet competes November 2009 for Miss Colorado 2010\n- Places: Fourth runner up\n\n**Question:** \"How did she qualify to compete?\""
      }
