            "side": "top",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Uncle Rick Is A Fraud\n\n### Lost License 2009\n\n**First Reason:** Didn't pay his dues\n\n**Candace's Theory:**\n\"My best guess is the reason he stopped paying his dues in Kentucky was that he was hoping they would stop their investigation into him.\n\nBut they didn't.\"\n\n### 2007: Investigation Opened\n\n**Reason #1: Multiple Mortgage Fraud**\n\nWhile employed by Bank of Corbin to perform title searches:\n- Rick didn't inform bank that **other mortgages already existed** on properties\n- They were issuing **loans to multiple people for the same property**\n- Resulted in Bank of Corbin issuing loans on **four properties already encumbered**\n\n**Candace's Note:**\n\"Just so you guys are clear, **this is exactly what led to the financial crisis**.\n\nYou ever seen the movie The Big Short? This is what happened.\"\n\n**Reason #2: Brother Bill's Stock Transfer**\n\nBill transferred 50% of stock in B&G Holdings LLC to:\n- \"Bill Urban Beck Children LLC\"\n- **Rick managed that LLC**\n\nWhile Rick was indebted to lending institutions:\n- Bill's stolen money went to LLC controlled by Rick\n- During bankruptcy court: \"Where's the money?\"\n- Answer: **In an LLC controlled by Rick**\n\n\"Rick ended up not only with Tony's money, but he also ended up with a good portion of Bill's money as well.\"\n\n**Reason #3: Deed Fraud**\n\nRick prepared deed transferring property to Anita Andrews:\n- Did NOT record deed with county\n- **Deed wasn't actually signed by Anita Andrews**\n- Then quickly transferred same property to his mother and father\n\n\"This kind of feels like deed fraud.\""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c3c3c3c3-c3c3-4c3c-8c3c-c3c3c3c3c3c3",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Two-Tiered Justice System",
      "position": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 2900
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 640,
      "color": "#880e4f",
