        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## \"Professional Negligence\" Not \"Criminality\"\n\n### The Verdict\n\n**August 2009:** Rick's license suspended (Kentucky only)\n\n**BUT:**\n\n\"They found that his actions did **not rise to the level of criminality**.\n\nJust **professional negligence**.\"\n\n### The Outrage\n\n**Candace's Response:**\n\n\"It's amazing. It is amazing what wealthy people, what wealthy criminals get away with, right?\n\nCould you just imagine the people whose entire lives got ruined because they believed in this company, they gave their money, they're doing mortgage, whatever it is, and then **banks are going under, their entire life savings have been depleted**.\n\nAnd we just look at the characters involved and he's working at Universal doing more LLCs with Lori.\n\nLori's working with the government.\n\n**There's no bar to entry when you're with the gang.**\n\nThe people that are running things doesn't matter. They write the laws. They'll read the laws if they want to read the laws.\n\nThis was professionally not okay. **He committed no crimes here. He just was negligent professionally.**\"\n\n### The Comparison\n\n**For Regular People:**\n- Too many parking tickets → jail\n- Speeding on freeway → jail, \"never get your life back,\" \"you've got a record\"\n- Smoking a joint → \"you got a record\"\n\n**For Hunter Biden:**\n- Smoking crack down freeway\n- Recording yourself\n- Hand in your own laptop\n- \"He's good. He's never going to see a day in prison.\"\n\n### The Reality\n\n\"Just wanted to let you know these are the people that rule over us.\n\nAnyways, enjoy your time at Universal Studios.\""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "d4d4d4d4-d4d4-4d4d-8d4d-d4d4d4d4d4d4",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Blake Neff's Shabbat Shalom Defense",
      "position": {
        "x": 1760,
        "y": -220
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 720,
      "color": "#ff6f00",
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "content",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Blake Breaks His Silence\n\n### What He Ignored\n\n**Everything Presented:**\n- Possible gang ties\n- Vince Lombardi connection\n- Tesseract school\n- Fraud following Lori\n- Money disappearing everywhere\n\n### What He COULDN'T Bear\n\n\"There was only one thing that Blake Nef could not bear.\n\nHe put his foot down last night and issued a **full-throated statement**.\n\n**No one comes for Shabbat Shalom.**\n\nNo one comes for Erica Shalom.\"\n\n### Blake's Statement\n\n\"I have avoided commenting on most of what Candace Owens claims... However, her last episode contains such a **blatant untruth about Charlie's daily life** that I feel compelled to correct it.\n\nCandace Owens aggressively ridicules Erica for using the phrase Shabbat Shalom and suggests that Charlie's last book, *Stop in the Name of God*, about the value of observing the Sabbath, is a fabrication to make Charlie appear more pro-Jewish and pro-Israel than he really was.\n\nIt is very revealing that Candace would fixate on this as it immediately reveals **unfamiliarity with Charlie's behavior** for the entire period that I knew him.\n\nCharlie was observing his evangelical Christian version of Shabbat.\"\n\n### Candace's Response\n\n\"Blake, I could show you text messages that **turning your phone off on Saturday I was doing first** and telling Charlie he should do before anybody.\n\nAs soon as I met George, that became a thing.\n\nI'm aware he turned his phone off on Saturdays. **I did it first.**\n\nWhat we're making fun of is that being the first thing that you hit on tour, the idea that he finished this book.\n\nIt's pretty obvious you guys were trying to make us remind us of how much Charlie loves Israel.\n\nBB Netanyahu came out within 48 hours to remind us of how much Charlie loved Israel.\n\nWe're aware of the psyop and **it failed**.\""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e5e5e5e5-e5e5-4e5e-8e5e-e5e5e5e5e5e5",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "The Dreidel Mockery",
      "position": {
        "x": 1760,
        "y": 560
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 520,
      "color": "#f57c00",
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "content",
          "position": {
            "side": "top",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Candace's Sarcastic Apology\n\n### The Mockery\n\n\"Everything Candace is saying... how dare she discount the fact that Charlie—\n\nI just want to be clear.\n\n**Charlie loved Dreidel. Dreidel. Dreidel. Dreidel.**\n\nHe made it out of clay.\n\nHe'd spin it. He'd play.\n\nHe loved **latkes**. Enough is enough.\n\nThey're delicious. They're crunchy. And they're salty.\n\n**And we will not stand for Candace to say this.**\"\n\n### The Apology\n\n\"I'm sorry, Blake.\n\nI'd like to apologize.\n\n**Shabbat shalom. Daddy's home.**\n\nHe threw in his phone.\n\nGlad we cleared that up.\n\nCharlie's phone was off on Saturdays.\n\nBro was like a rapper sliding in like Usher.\n\n**Daddy's home. Shalom.**\n\nI'm sorry. I'm sorry, Erica. And I'm sorry, Blake.\n\nI will never do this again.\"\n\n### The Clarification\n\n**Later:**\n\n\"Just to be clear, I do love latkes.\n\nThey are delicious. They are very, very good and they are salty.\n\nSo there's that. We can meet in the middle.\n\n**Blake, you better be Jewish.**\n\nIf I find out you're not Jewish, you're in so much trouble.\""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "f6f6f6f6-f6f6-4f6f-8f6f-f6f6f6f6f6f6",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "The Web They Weave",
      "position": {
        "x": 1760,
        "y": 1140
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 640,
      "color": "#1b5e20",
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "content",
          "position": {
            "side": "top",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## \"They All Knew Each Other Before\"\n\n### Candace's Theory\n\n**The Connections:**\n\n\"I feel like you and Lori and Tyler **go back way back**.\n\nI feel like you guys have known each other for like since at least **2010** if I'm being honest.\n\nI think you knew the Farnsworths and I think you knew the Boyers.\n\nI'd actually go back further.\n\nI think you guys maybe even knew each other since **Afghanistan**.\n\nBut I'm going to wait until tomorrow to introduce that and how you guys maybe even could have known each other.\n\nJust dancing around each other there in Arizona, all getting involved in the same stuff, **charter schools**, and then you and Tyler are going to graduate in the same year.\n\nIt's all so crazy.\"\n\n### The Airport Story\n\n\"Tell me what happened. What happened with Turning Point USA?\n\nYou just knew, got lucky. We're on a pilgrimage, I guess, and there Charlie was at the airport in Israel.\n\nYou saw him. Your mom said go up to him. **She's a pusher, right? Lori's a pusher.**\n\nI always thought it was so strange how you never mentioned that I was at the airport with Charlie.\n\nJust thought that was so weird. You never said that.\n\n**I saw Charlie with Candace because we were actually together for that trip.**\n\nSo interesting.\"\n\n### The Conclusion\n\n\"It's a tangled web that we weave, Erica.\"\n\n**Final Theory:**\n\n\"I think tomorrow you will see even more how plausible that is.\n\nHow plausible it is that **they all kind of knew each other before** and then **surrounded Charlie like a November Renaissance**.\""
      }
    }
